    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-12-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-12-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="844"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d844">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 2491/47.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Squiers</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-12-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 24, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to your instructions 77, December 24, 1907, and 137, December 1, 1908,
                    minister for foreign affairs advises me that his Government accepts in principle
                    submission of the boundary question between Panama and Costa Rica to impartial
                    arbitration of the Chief Justice of the United States, but wishes to know which
                    questions are to be submitted. The Government is inclined to adhere to boundary
                    line as fixed upon by the Loubet award and article 3 of the constitution.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Squiers.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
